WHO   — THE TRANSFORMER STACK — a niphelektron sphere — the inference pipeline
WHAT  — Now a stack of identical layers goes to work on the sequence of vectors. The engine of each layer is attention: every token looks at every other and pulls in what is relevant, mixing the sequence so each position becomes a blend of its context. Stacked dozens deep, this is where the model's 'thinking' happens — and where the T in GPT comes from.
WHERE — the inference layer — a stage of the pipeline  Framework inputs: the stream; the token; the vector; the layer  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
